  "rationale": "This supervisor structure prioritizes rapid marker acquisition and approach, robust obstacle avoidance, and safe, non-oscillatory recovery. It uses helper states for commit actions (forward, rotate, scan, marker tracking) and ensures all uncontrollable events are handled deterministically. After obstacle encounters, recovery passes through a scan state before resuming exploration. Marker tracking is prioritized when marker_seen, and search alternates between short forward moves and scans. Terminal goal state is entered on marker_close.",
